This paper analyzes real-world SPARQL queries, which are used to query RDF data. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the database (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR) categories. Additionally, the paper analyzes the structure and syntax of the queries, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.DL) categories. Finally, the paper could also be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) as it discusses query evaluation engines and performance tuning.
